items.title: Awesome Cheminformatics
items.content_text:
### Libraries / Format Checking

*   [ChEMBL\_Structure\_Pipeline (formerly standardiser) (⭐209)](https://github.com/chembl/ChEMBL_Structure_Pipeline) - Tool designed to provide a simple way of standardising molecules as a prelude to e.g. molecular modelling exercises.

### Libraries / Machine Learning

*   [ChemML (⭐168)](https://github.com/hachmannlab/chemml) - ChemML is a machine learning and informatics program suite for the analysis, mining, and modeling of chemical and materials data. (based on Tensorflow)
*   [chemmodlab (⭐17)](https://github.com/jrash/ChemModLab) - A Cheminformatics Modeling Laboratory for Fitting and Assessing Machine Learning Models in R.

### Libraries / Others

*   [OPSIN (⭐179)](https://github.com/dan2097/opsin) - Open Parser for Systematic IUPAC nomenclature

### Resources / Courses

*   [Cheminformatics OLCC](https://chem.libretexts.org/Courses/Intercollegiate_Courses/Cheminformatics_OLCC_\(2019\)) - Cheminformatics course of the Collaborative Intercollegiate Online Chemistry Course (OLCC) course of University of Arkansas at Little Rock by Robert Belford

items.title: Awesome R
items.content_text: ### Data Formats * [vroom (⭐630)](https://github.com/r-lib/vroom) - Fast reading of delimited files. * [arrow ](https://arrow.apache.org/docs/r/) - An interface to the Arrow C++ library. * [feather (⭐2.7k)](https://github.com/wesm/feather) - Fast, interoperable binary data frame storage for Python, R, and more powered by Apache Arrow. * [fst ](https://github.com/qinwf/awesome-R/blob/master/README.md/www.fstpackage.org/fst/) - Lightning Fast Serialization of Data Frames for R. * [haven (⭐441)](https://github.com/hadley/haven) - Improved methods to import SPSS, Stata and SAS files in R. * [jsonlite (⭐388)](https://github.com/jeroenooms/jsonlite) - A robust and quick way to parse JSON files in R. * [qs (⭐426)](https://github.com/traversc/qs) - Quick serialization of R objects. * [readxl ](https://readxl.tidyverse.org/) - Read excel files (.xls and .xlsx) into R. * [readr (⭐1k)](https://github.com/hadley/readr) - A fast and friendly way to read tabular data into R. * [rio (⭐615)](https://github.com/leeper/rio) - A Swiss-Army Knife for Data I/O. * [readODS (⭐0)](https://github.com/chainsawriot/readODS/) - Read OpenDocument Spreadsheets into R as data.frames. * [RcppTOML (⭐38)](https://github.com/eddelbuettel/rcpptoml) - Rcpp Bindings to C++ parser for TOML files. * [writexl](https://docs.ropensci.org/writexl/) - Portable, light-weight data frame to xlsx exporter for R. * [yaml (⭐167)](https://github.com/viking/r-yaml) - R package for converting objects to and from YAML.
items.content_html:
Data Formats

  • vroom (⭐630) - Fast reading of delimited files.
  • arrow - An interface to the Arrow C++ library.
  • feather (⭐2.7k) - Fast, interoperable binary data frame storage for Python, R, and more powered by Apache Arrow.
  • fst - Lightning Fast Serialization of Data Frames for R.
  • haven (⭐441) - Improved methods to import SPSS, Stata and SAS files in R.
  • jsonlite (⭐388) - A robust and quick way to parse JSON files in R.
  • qs (⭐426) - Quick serialization of R objects.
  • readxl - Read excel files (.xls and .xlsx) into R.
  • readr (⭐1k) - A fast and friendly way to read tabular data into R.
  • rio (⭐615) - A Swiss-Army Knife for Data I/O.
  • readODS (⭐0) - Read OpenDocument Spreadsheets into R as data.frames.
  • RcppTOML (⭐38) - Rcpp Bindings to C++ parser for TOML files.
  • writexl - Portable, light-weight data frame to xlsx exporter for R.
  • yaml (⭐167) - R package for converting objects to and from YAML.
